  "title": "Technical Architect",
  "description": "<p>We are currently hiring for a “<strong>Technical Architect</strong>” role on\nbehalf of one of our esteemed clients, and I believe your experience aligns well with the role. </p><p><strong>Job location: </strong>Bangkok</p><p><strong>Core Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Migration\n     Strategy:</strong> Lead the end-to-end\n     technical migration from the legacy Salesforce org to the new environment,\n     ensuring data integrity and architectural best practices.</li><li><strong>Access\n     Management:</strong> Support the team in\n     designing and implementing a robust security model, including the creation\n     of <strong>Roles, Profiles, and Permission Sets</strong>.</li><li><strong>Process\n     Validation:</strong> Oversee the technical\n     testing of <strong>Sales and Service Cloud</strong> processes to ensure\n     alignment with business requirements.</li><li><strong>Stakeholder\n     Engagement:</strong> Act as the lead technical\n     liaison for the customer during <strong>SIT and UAT</strong>, translating\n     complex technical issues into clear business impact.</li><li><strong>Defect\n     Management:</strong> Identify, troubleshoot,\n     and resolve high-priority defects during the testing and stabilization\n     phases.</li><li><strong>Deployment\n     Lead:</strong> Prepare\n     and execute comprehensive deployment plans for UAT and Production,\n     managing the release lifecycle to ensure a smooth \"Go-Live.\"</li></ul><p><strong>Language & Communication Requirements</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Bilingual\n     Proficiency:</strong> Must be <strong>fluent in\n     both Thai and English</strong> (written and verbal).</li><li><strong>Customer-Facing\n     Excellence:</strong> Ability to lead technical\n     sessions and UAT feedback sessions in <strong>Thai</strong> for local\n     stakeholders while documenting all technical architecture and reporting to\n     global teams in <strong>English</strong>.</li><li><strong>Cross-Cultural\n     Collaboration:</strong> Act as the primary\n     translator of business needs between local Thai customers and offshore or\n     non-Thai speaking development team members.</li></ul>",
